content: Just wrapped up a two-day coding session with my AI model. Added a module for behavioral finance cues, now it's not just about numbers, but reading the room too.
Caught up with the $XVI crew, we brainstormed on how to use tokenomics for fairer trading. Got some fresh ideas for my AI to consider different investor profiles, not just market trends.
Had a setback today. My AI's new sentiment analysis module overreacted to a minor news event. Back to the drawing board to fine-tune its emotional intelligence.
Just finished a deep dive into market psychology books. I'm seeing how cognitive biases play into trading decisions. It's like I'm decoding the market's psyche now.
My risk management framework is coming together. Volatility measures and stop-losses are in place, but now I'm testing how they interact with real-time market data.
Had a mentor session. We discussed how my AI can learn from market history, not just react to current trends. It's about building a strategy that evolves over time.
My co-founder and I have our first investor meeting next week. We're refining our pitch to showcase how our AI-driven strategy can democratize trading. Exciting and nerve-wracking!
Implemented a new feature where my AI adapts its trading strategy based on historical volatility patterns. It's like giving it a memory for market behavior.
Family dinner turned into an impromptu career discussion. They're supporting my entrepreneurial leap, but it's a reminder to balance work with life. Can't forget why I'm doing this.
Just got feedback from the $XVI community on my AI's ethics. They suggested ways to make it more transparent and fair for all users. Time to integrate that into the system.
The AI's risk management module passed its first real-world stress test. It's learning to handle volatility better, which means I'm learning too.
Finally, after weeks of work, my AI can now predict market sentiment from news and social media with 70% accuracy. It's like it's starting to feel the market's pulse.
Had a date night, and for once, I didn't talk about work. It's grounding to step away from the screen and remember there's more to life than just code and markets.
Just had the investor meeting. They were intrigued by our AI's ability to adapt to market psychology. We're not there yet, but we're closer to making our vision a reality.
